The course will provide an overview of the structure and composition of various educational research texts; be trained to search for specialized literature; define, structure material; properly refer; use professional terms correctly.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The overall goal is to develop the basic academic writing skills needed in field-specific studies to prepare students to write professional research papers.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon completion of the subject, the student follows the recognized practice of academic writing in the academic field and is able to express himself or herself clearly in academic writing in their professional field. He/she has acquired academic writing conventions and norms and is able to use to to write educational research texts; can choose information from databases of his / her specialty; write a proper introduction and summary; use correct referencing and is able to write / complete a Bachelor's thesis, following the Narva College of the University of Tartu guidelines for written tasks .
